Pre-heat your oven to 200 degrees and bring a #pot of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp}. Pop the @British chicken thighs{8} on a #baking tray and season with a generous pinch of @salt{}, a good grind of @black pepper{} and @olive oil{1%tbsp}. Strip the @thyme{3%sprigs} leaves from their stalks using your thumb and first finger. Sprinkle half of the thyme leaves over the chicken thighs and then massage in. Roast the chicken thighs on the top shelf of your oven for ~{40%minutes}.

With the chicken in your oven, get on with the rest of the prep. Cut the @new potatoes{2} in half and pop them into the boiling water. Cook for ~{10%minutes} until half cooked and then drain in a #colander.

Cut the @red onion{1} in half through the root, peel and then slice into half moon shapes roughly 1cm thick. Put the red onion on another #baking tray and drizzle over @olive oil{1%tbsp}. Add the par-cooked potatoes, the leftover thyme leaves and @salt{1/2%tsp}. Mix well and then pop in the centre of your oven to cook for ~{25%minutes}.

Cut the @radish{1} in half. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}. Tip: Use a #garlic press if you have one! Rinse the @baby spinach{6%leaves} under cold water in a #colander.

Pop the radishes into a #pot and cover with @water{200%ml}. Add a pinch of @salt{} and @?sugar{2%tsp} (if you have some). Bring the pot to the boil, reduce the heat to medium and cook the radishes for ~water{10%minutes}. The water should evaporate by two-thirds in this time. Once your radishes are tender, remove from the heat. We will mix in the butter later.

When your chicken and potatoes are golden and cooked through, remove them from your oven and get on with the spinach. Heat a #frying pan on medium heat and add half of the @Netherend salted butter{2%tbsp} and the grated garlic. Once the butter has melted add the spinach leaves to the pan, stir and then pop on a #lid. Cook for another ~{2%minutes} until the leaves are wilted. Season with a generous pinch of @salt{} and a good grind of @black pepper{}.

Warm the radishes over a medium heat and mix in the remaining butter so as they are nicely glazed.

Serve your chicken on top of a generous serving of roast potatoes. Pop some spinach and radishes alongside. Finish with a dollop of the @lemon mayonnaise{6%tsp} and tuck in!

> Drum roll please for our British Veggie of the Month - it's the ravishing radish! André says "This is a really cool way of cooking radish which a lot of people don't think of."

> Fancy transforming radish from a salad veggie to a deliciously warm, buttery side? André is an absolute genius!

> If you have a garlic press, use it to grate the garlic easily.